96,Château Pichon Longueville Lalande Pauillac-,"Saturated with dark currant, fig and blackberry compote flavors, this has a fleshy, nearly glycerin feel at first before stretching out to reveal singed cedar, tobacco leaf, dark earth and cassis bush flavors. A terrific tug of cast iron emerges at the very end. Deliciously juicy dark fruit keeps rolling throughout. Best from 2025 through 2040. 12,000 cases made. —JM",2016,197 ,97.0,3
97,Wine & Soul Douro Manoella-,"Zesty currant and boysenberry notes are tangy and inviting in this spicy, medium-bodied red, with moderate tannins supporting the herb, tea and mineral details on the finish. Touriga Nacional, Touriga Franca, Tinta Roriz and Touriga Francesa. Drink now through 2023. 2,000 cases made, 250 cases imported. —GS",2016,22 ,90.0,3
98,Domaines Dominique Piron Morgon Côte du Py-,"A vivid minerally undertone marks the pure raspberry and ripe cherry flavors, accented by licorice and floral details that give way to white pepper and wild herb elements on the long, lightly tannic finish. Drink now through 2024. 3,000 cases made, 200 cases imported. —GS",2017,28 ,92.0,3
99,Domaine du Castel Grand Vin Haute-Judée-,"Ripe currant, blackberry and plum flavors are nicely displayed with mocha, baking spice and cedar details in this sinewy, focused red. Hints of olive and graphite mark the tannic finish. Drink now through 2025. 3,900 cases made, 1,280 cases imported. —GS",2016,85 ,91.0,3
